Open-source metadata and tagging inspirations

Some metadata, tagging, file-organization, and library-management
workflows in Michi Music Player were conceptually informed by open-source
music software such as MusicBrainz Picard, beets, Kid3, puddletag,
EasyTAG, Quod Libet / Ex Falso, Clementine, Strawberry Music Player,
MusicBrainz, AcoustID, Chromaprint, and Mutagen.

These references are conceptual, architectural, or workflow references
only unless a file-level notice states otherwise. No source code, icons,
logos, screenshots, UI assets, databases, or documentation text from
those projects is intentionally included in Michi Music Player.

Local network synchronization inspirations

Michi Sync was conceptually inspired by local-network discovery and
transfer workflows found in applications such as LocalSend, as well as
historical device synchronization workflows associated with desktop music
libraries and portable music players.

This is a conceptual reference only. No LocalSend source code, assets,
icons, branding, or protocol implementation is intentionally included
unless a file-level notice says otherwise.

Music-library and playback inspirations

Michi Music Player may include independently implemented ideas commonly
found in music software, including visual album browsing, playlist
management, smart mixes, metadata editing, library search, server
browsing, internet radio, local playback, multiroom playback, and device
synchronization.

Conceptual references may include iTunes, iPod-era device management,
Apple Music, Roon, TIDAL, Spotify, Deezer Flow, Every Noise at Once,
Audirvana, Clementine, Strawberry Music Player, Quod Libet, and similar
music applications.

These references do not imply affiliation, endorsement, copying, or
compatibility with every feature of those products.

Integration and compatibility targets

Michi Music Player may optionally interoperate with external systems such
as Home Assistant, Snapcast, Navidrome, Jellyfin, Subsonic-compatible
servers, MusicBrainz, AcoustID, AudD, Shazam-compatible libraries,
LRCLIB, Wikipedia/Wikimedia, GStreamer, Qt/PySide, KDE/Plasma, Avahi,
PipeWire, PulseAudio, ALSA, and other user-configured services or tools.

Compatibility or integration does not imply endorsement, certification,
partnership, or inclusion of their source code.

Users, packagers, and distributors are responsible for complying with the
licenses, API terms, rate limits, attribution requirements, trademark
rules, and data-use policies of each external service or dependency.

